<Layout title="Professional Advisors · Mortgages for Attorneys, Financial Planners, CPAs, Mortgage Brokers &amp; Insurance Agency Owners — Practice Ownership Multi-Source Florida Qualifying" description="Florida professional advisor client hub for attorneys licensed by The Florida Bar across BigLaw equity partners + regional practice partners + solo practitioners with W-2 base + partnership K-1 distributions + capital distributions + book of business in M&A and corporate and real estate and litigation and family and tax and estate practice areas; financial planners credentialed by CFP Board with Series 65/66 licensure operating fiduciary RIA practice under Investment Advisers Act 1940 with AUM-based recurring revenue at typical 1.0-1.25% annual + estate planning fees + insurance trail commission stream; CPAs licensed by Florida Board of Accountancy with AICPA + FICPA membership operating S-corp owner + partnership member + sole practitioner structures with recurring annual engagements covering audit + tax + compilation + advisory work and PE consolidator practice acquisition opportunities; mortgage brokers under NMLS with Florida OFR registration earning loan origination commission per loan closed + book of business override on team production + firm equity for owners; insurance agency owners licensed by Florida OIR + Florida CFO/DFS with substantial in-force book renewal trail commission stream + new business commission + agency equity value typically 1.5-3.5x trail multiple for ownership transitions. Multi-source income synthesis under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income with 2-year history + continuity narrative; B3-3.2-01 self-employed borrower documentation with Form 1084 cash-flow analysis adding back depreciation + amortization + business mileage + business use of home + entity-level non-cash expenses; B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp documentation for K-1 income from practice equity stakes with partnership agreement excerpt and 2-year K-1 schedules; Bank Statement Non-QM alternative qualifying on 12-24 months business bank statement deposits; P&L Statement Non-QM qualifying on CPA-prepared profit and loss statement for established practice owners; Asset-Depletion Non-QM converting liquid portfolio balance to implied monthly income amortized over 360 months for HNW retiring partners + practice sellers; DSCR Debt Service Coverage Ratio Non-QM qualifying on property rental income alone for investment property portfolio scaling beyond personal qualifying capacity; Conventional Conforming and Jumbo with documented borrower qualifying; Cash-Out Refinance for practice acquisition and expansion. Recurring revenue economics with retainers + CPA recurring annual engagements + financial planner AUM fees + insurance renewal trail + mortgage broker book overrides supporting continuity narrative. PE-backed consolidator wave continuing across RIA wealth management, CPA practices, insurance agency rollups at 6-12x annual recurring revenue valuations. Florida HNW + UHNW wealth migration sustaining advisor practice demand. 2026 federal estate exemption sunset from $13.99M (2025) to approximately $7M per person absent Congressional extension creating material estate planning urgency through 2025 for HNW advisor practice owners. Five sub-page categories with dedicated content in production: attorney, financial-planner, cpas-accountant, mortgage-broker, insurance-agency-owner." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-advisors/">
